args:
While Ieyasu can use the curious power of a
soulpact to shapeshift, he only came to Alberia
to spread New Year's cheer to another nation.
For some reason, however, Botan has a bone
to pick with him. Before they come to blows,
a voice rings out to stop them.
And with that, the task is complete.
Good people of Alberia, I pray you were\nunharmed by those horrid fiends?
But if I may, who ARE all of you?
Permit me to formally introduce myself.\nI am Ieyasu of Hinomoto, leader of one\nof the Twelve Wyrmclans.
These are my attendants,\nAddis and Sazanka.
It gladdens me to make your acquaintance.
Then you must be the people Botan told\nus about.
To interfere with you, buddy!\nNow get your butt back to Hinomoto!
You'd raise a hand against your master?\nSeems like a good way to lose it.
Indeed, it will not do to make a scene in\nfront of the very people to whom we are\nattempting to show hospitality.

Indeed! The providing of hospitality is
extremely important in our culture,
and so we have come from Hinomoto
in order to deliver fortune and cheer.
Your castle is really quite wonderful.\nA splendid edifice.
Thank you. It's quite an honor to be praised\nby a foreign leader.
On the contrary, we are grateful for the\nkindness you have shown after we so\nsuddenly appeared at your door.
Though I must admit, I was rather shocked\nto learn that someone from another land\ncould also form pacts with dragons.
I share in your surprise; never did I think\nto find another royal line with a power\nsimilar to our soulpacts.
So ＂soulpact＂ is your term for what we\ncall a dragonpact, yes?
Just so. In our land, soulpacts are\npermitted for the shogun and heads\nof the Wyrmclans alone.
So are you this shogun guy, then?
No, I am but a candidate for the position.\nAt the moment, I merely lead one of\nthe Twelve Wyrmclans.
The successor family is comprised of\ntwelve branches, and the heads of each\nare candidates to become shogun.
Guess that's why you call yourselves the\nTwelve Wyrmclans.
You have the right of it. Also, it may\ninterest you to know that the duty of the\nTwelve Wyrmclans is threefold.
First, we fight to protect Hinomoto using\nthe power granted us by the soulpact.
Second, we govern our various territories.\nAnd third, we are responsible for the\nfestivals honoring Amaterasu.
And so, we have come to this land in order\nto hold the largest of said festivals, which\nis a celebration of the new year.
Ah, so that's what you meant when you\nsaid you'd come to deliver fortune.
Indeed, for in Hinomoto, New Year's Day\nis one where Amaterasu brings luck and\ncheer to all of our people.
At some point in time, it was decided that\nthis fortune should be shared with all,\nand not merely kept for ourselves.
And that job fell to Master Ieyasu and the\nother heads of the Twelve Wyrmclans.

Allow me to speak plain: We wish to
deliver New Year's greetings and share
our celebration of the holiday with
those from other lands.
In that case, we'd be happy to have you.
Hmph! I'm bringing my own fun New Year,\nso they don't need YOURS!
You were doin' just fine sittin' over there\nall quiet-like earlier.
You must really wanna be cut down.
Ha! Like I'm scared of you.
Fine, I'll back off—but only if you\ngo back home and let ME handle\nthe hospitality here!
It's gonna be WAY better than whatever\nthose stiff old Wyrmclans do!
